StaticPage.create(name: "home", title: "Welcome!", content:"<section>
<p>Welcome to the Quillective! I'm your host, Jessy - a hot-headed, heart-rate-monitored, fail-counting, variety caster of new releases or cult classics. Relating the gaming content back to real life issues is my speciality.</p>
<p>I've been playing video games since I could sit up. Mario Bros. for the Nintendo was my first game and console. I enjoyed speedrunning or casually scrolling through out it when I was a toddler. Eventually, I added the PlayStation to my arsenal, albeit with only Crash Bandicoot and Rayman. Throughout this time, I was glued to my Game Boy Color or Game Boy Advance SP, especially when Pokemon was involved. After a small stint on the original XBOX with the Halo series, Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic, and Mass Effect, I turned to PC Gaming where World of Warcraft dominated hours of my life daily. Eventually, after many of my friends moved or graduated, I began livestreaming my gaming in order to connect with other people, similar to the feeling of playing on the couch with a sibling or friend.  </p>
<p>Unconditionally, video games are my passion, muse, hobby, obsession, and freedom. Without gaming, I wouldn't have the relationships I have now. Yes, video games are art. Yes, we can learn educational lessons from video games. No, video games are not a cancer on society.</p>
<p>If you're interested in hearing my rambles live, or would like to read way-too-serious analyses of video games, or see my amateur photography, stay a while and listen.</p>
</section>")

